SLUGROUTE PROJECT ACCOMPLISHMENTS - COMPLETED TASKS

### Phase 1: Python Scraper & Data Engineering
1. Session Reliability: Implemented a requests session with a 5-retry strategy and backoff.
2. HTML Parsing: Integrated BeautifulSoup to navigate complex UCSC PISA table structures.
3. Course Code Extraction: Built a regex to extract codes (e.g. "CSE 115A") from header strings.
4. Title Sanitization: Created logic to isolate the Course Title from raw metadata strings.
5. Meeting Day Splitting: Developed a parser to separate "MWF" from time-strings like "10:40AM".
6. Meeting Time Parsing: Structured logic to convert raw time strings into "Start-End" formats.
7. Building Name Isolation: Wrote regex to strip room numbers (e.g. "Thimann Lab 001" -> "Thimann Lab").
8. Room Number Extraction: Created a secondary field specifically for room numbers/codes.
9. Status Cleaning: Wrote code to remove duplicate "Cancelled" or "Open" status text from cells.
10. Panel Body Navigation: Built logic to dive into "Associated Discussion" panels within the HTML.
11. Section ID Regex: Developed regex to capture unique Section IDs (e.g. "02A") and Class Numbers.
12. Virtual Filter: Implemented logic to flag "Online" or "Remote" instruction types.
13. Staff Fallback: Created a "Staff" placeholder for courses without assigned instructors.
14. Multi-Term Scraping: Configured loops to scrape Winter 2026 (2260) and Spring 2026 (2262).
15. Polling Delay: Implemented a 0.2s delay between requests to remain polite to servers.
16. Detailed Class Fetching: Engineered a two-step process: search results, then individual details.
17. Database Initialization: Wrote a script to generate the SQLite file and schema from scratch.
18. Timestamping: Added a last_updated column to track data freshness per record.

### Phase 2: Database & Geodata Normalization
19. Relational Schema: Designed a 3-table structure (Courses, Lectures, Sections) for performance.
20. Coordinate Dataset: Compiled 100+ Latitude/Longitude pairs for UCSC landmarks.
21. Uppercase Normalization: Wrote import script forcing building names to UPPERCASE to prevent join errors.
22. Trailing Space Removal: Used .strip() logic on all building names during database migration.
23. Primary Key Constraints: Set up unique IDs on (class_number, term) to prevent duplication.
24. Foreign Key Integrity: Established links between the lectures table and the parent courses table.
25. SQL Spatial Joins: Wrote complex SQL queries in Go that merge schedules with geodata on the fly.
26. Missing Data Handling: Used IFNULL(lat, 0) in SQL to prevent frontend crashes on unmapped buildings.
27. Off-Campus Filtering: Created a specific list for "Silicon Valley" and "Harbor" coordinates.
28. Atomic Commit Logic: Programmed the database to commit changes per course for data durability.

### Phase 3: Go Backend API Development
29. Gin Router Setup: Initialized the Go Gin framework for high-concurrency routing.
30. Dynamic API Routing: Built the /api/course/:term/:code endpoint for flexible querying.
31. Go Struct Mapping: Defined strict Meeting and Offering structs to ensure type-safe JSON.
32. SQL Row Scanning: Developed logic to map SQLite row results into nested Go objects.
33. Section Aggregation: Wrote a secondary SQL pass to attach DIS/LAB meetings to their parent LEC.
34. Static File Serving: Configured http.FileServer to host the frontend assets on the same port.
35. CGO Integration: Configured the build environment to support the SQLite3 C-driver.
36. Error Payload Design: Standardized JSON error messages for frontend debugging.
37. Graceful DB Closing: Implemented defer db.Close() to ensure connection safety.
38. URL Encoding Support: Enabled the API to handle course codes with spaces (e.g. CSE 12).
39. Internal Logging: Added log.Println statements to monitor incoming API requests.
40. Server Health Check: Configured the server to launch on localhost:8080 with a live status message.

### Phase 4: Frontend UI & Layout
41. UCSC Blue/Gold Theme: Created a CSS :root system using official university hex codes.
42. Responsive Flexbox Layout: Designed a layout that adapts the map size to the browser window.
43. Collapsible Sidebar: Built a toggleable menu to hide/show course results and save space.
44. Fixed Navbar: Implemented a z-indexed navbar that stays at the top during scrolling.
45. Inter Font Integration: Integrated the Google Inter typeface for a clean, modern look.
46. Course Card Design: Built a custom Card UI for search results with dynamic border colors.
47. Brand Identity: Added the "SlugRoute" logo text and slug emoji branding.
48. Empty State UI: Created a "No results found" visual placeholder for initial entry.
49. Action Buttons: Designed "Heart" (Save) and "X" (Remove) buttons for result management.
50. Visual Legend: Built a sidebar legend explaining the Star, Square, and Circle icons.
51. Card Highlighting: Developed a glow effect for cards when their map pins are hovered.
52. Sidebar Scroll Management: Added an independent scroll container for the results list.

### Phase 5: Google Maps & Interaction Logic
53. Advanced Marker Integration: Integrated Google Maps AdvancedMarkerElement for vector support.
54. Custom SVG Pathing: Wrote JS logic to draw distinct Star, Square, and Circle paths.
55. Vector Map ID: Configured a specific mapId to enable custom tilt and hybrid styling.
56. Campus Geofencing: Implemented UCSC_BOUNDS to prevent users from panning off-campus.
57. Building-Based Clustering: Built a grouping algorithm so one pin holds multiple classes.
58. Star Priority Logic: Programmed pins to show a Star if any meeting in that building is a Lecture.
59. Dynamic Color Manager: Built a JS system to assign 20+ unique colors to different courses.
60. Auto-Pan & Fit: Coded map.fitBounds() to automatically frame all search results.
61. Rich InfoWindows: Designed HTML popups that show Instructor, Time, and Room data.
62. Search-on-Enter: Added a key listener so pressing "Enter" triggers the search.
63. Map Focus Zoom: Programmed a 17x zoom when clicking specific sidebar results.
64. Marker Recycling: Wrote logic to clear old markers before rendering new search results.
65. Async Library Loading: Used google.maps.importLibrary for faster initial page loads.
66. Event Delegation: Attached click listeners to pins to open info popups automatically.
67. Type-Based Filtering: Built logic to toggle markers based on LEC/LAB/DIS checkboxes.
68. Color Persistence: Ensured a course keeps the same color throughout its lifecycle on the map.
69. Marker Stroke Optimization: Added a white stroke to SVG icons for visibility on satellite views.
70. Shadow Effects: Applied CSS filters to pins to give them a 3D lift off the map.

